OL,3,CFather of Southport killer tells
OL,4,Cinquiry he was frightened of violent
OL,5,Cson
OL,7,FThe father of the Southport killer has
OL,8,Ftold a public inquiry he bears his
OL,9,F"share of the responsibility" for the
OL,10,Fattack but said he was frightened of
OL,11,Fhis teenage son.
OL,13,FGiving evidence to Liverpool Town Hall
OL,14,Ffrom a remote location Alphonse R told
OL,15,Fthe public inquiry his son, AR, would
OL,16,Fhave "random" outbursts of violence,
OL,17,Fsometimes twice a day.
