OL,5,Cson
OL,7,FAlphonse R accepted he later
OL,8,Fcomplained to Childline about
OL,9,Fbreaching his son's confidentiality.
OL,11,FHe said: "He went to them asking for
OL,12,Fhelp because he was struggling with
OL,13,Fdark thoughts that he was having of
OL,14,Fusing a knife and they reported him to
OL,15,Fthe police."
OL,17,FMr Moss suggested that instead of
OL,18,Fhelping agencies who were trying to
OL,19,Fdeal with his son's violence he "went
OL,20,Fon the attack" and undermined them.
