OL,7,FAlphonse R replied: "Our son was
OL,8,Fpermanently excluded and I knew that
OL,9,Fthings were going to get worse, and
OL,10,Fthey have."
OL,12,FAfter his exclusion, AR was sent to
OL,13,Fpupil referral unit The Acorns School.
OL,15,FHeadteacher Joanne Hodson told the
OL,16,Finquiry in earlier evidence AR's
OL,17,Fparents did not "flinch" during a
OL,18,Fmeeting when the teenager said he had
OL,19,Ftaken a knife to school and intended
OL,20,Fto use it.
