OL,3,CFather of Southport killer tells
OL,4,Cinquiry he was frightened of violent
OL,5,Cson
OL,7,FHe said he thought referrals to the
OL,8,FGovernment's anti-terror programme
OL,9,FPrevent by the Acorns were
OL,10,F"malicious", but by the time of the
OL,11,Ffirst referral, in December 2019, he
OL,12,Fhad "lost control" of his son.
OL,14,FHe said: "I had no authority as a
OL,15,Ffather."
OL,17,FAlphonse R said he was not aware that
OL,18,Fon a tablet at home his son was
OL,19,Faccessing images of torture,
OL,20,Fantisemitic and anti-Islamic material
OL,21,Fand images of Nazi mass graves.
